## Fuzzy Hashing ##

calcs>dir
calcs>md5deep

# Compute the fuzzy hash of all files
C:> ssdeep –b * 
{-b : only display file name only; suppress path}

# Matching against a given fuzzy hash
C:> ssdeep –b calc_win7_32bit.exe > calc_32bit_fuzzyHash.txt  
C:> ssdeep –b –m calc_32bit_fuzzyHash.txt  *

# Matching against a set of other known files
C:> ssdeep –b C:Windows\SysWOW64\*.exe > WOW64_exes_fHash.txt  
C:> ssdeep –b –m WOW64_exes_fHash.txt <insert some directory> *
*** Note the 3-byte (bit) change in the modified calc – DOS -> dos  ***

# {Matching against all files even if there is a 0% match}
use the –a switch
